definition: A member of the class of animals Aves in the phylum Chordata, characterized by being warm-blooded, having feathers and wings usually capable of flight, and laying eggs.
To observe or identify wild birds in their natural environment.
Fast growing function based on Kruskal's tree theorem.

A perennial woody plant, not exactly defined, but differentiated from a shrub by its larger size (typically over a few meters in height) or growth habit, usually having a single (or few) main axis or trunk unbranched for some distance above the ground and a head of branches and foliage.
To chase (an animal or person) up a tree.
A wheeled vehicle that moves independently, with at least three wheels, powered mechanically, steered by a driver and mostly for personal transportation.
A solid or hollow sphere, or roughly spherical mass.
To form or wind into a ball.

An appeal by the crowd for holding the ball against a tackled player. This is heard almost any time an opposition player is tackled, without regard to whether the rules about "prior opportunity" to dispose of the ball are fulfilled.
An item of furniture used to sit on or in, comprising a seat, legs, back, and sometimes arm rests, for use by one person. Compare stool, couch, sofa, settee, loveseat and bench.
To act as chairperson at; to preside over.
A chairman or chairwoman, someone who presides over a meeting, board, etc.
A chair-like device used for performing execution by electrocution.
An animal of the family Felidae:
To hoist (the anchor) by its ring so that it hangs at the cathead.
A mammal, Canis familiaris or Canis lupus familiaris, that has been domesticated for thousands of years, of highly variable appearance due to human breeding.
To pursue with the intent to catch.
Meat from a dog eaten as food.
A common, round fruit produced by the tree Malus domestica, cultivated in temperate climates.
To become apple-like.
Furniture with a top surface to accommodate a variety of uses.
To tabulate; to put into a table or grid.
A collection of sheets of paper bound together to hinge at one edge, containing printed or written material, pictures, etc.
A dairy product made from curdled or cultured milk.
To prepare curds for making cheese.
Said while being photographed, to give the impression of smiling.
An elongated curved tropical fruit that grows in bunches and has a creamy flesh and a smooth skin.
Curved like a banana, especially of a ball in flight.
A colour/color that is a dark blend of red and blue; dark magenta.
To turn purple in colour.
Having a colour/color that is a dark blend of red and blue.
A recreational drug based on cough syrup, popular in the hip-hop community in the southern United States.
An evergreen tree of the genus Citrus such as Citrus sinensis.

Having the colour of the fruit of an orange tree; yellowred; reddish-yellow.

A physician; a member of the medical profession; one who is trained and licensed to heal the sick or injured. The final examination and qualification may award a doctor degree in which case the post-nominal letters are D.O., DPM, M.D., DMD, DDS, in the US or MBBS in the UK.
To act as a medical doctor to.
A person who teaches, especially one employed in a school.
An outdoor area containing one or more types of plants, usually plants grown for food or ornamental purposes.
To grow plants in a garden; to create or maintain a garden.

The inedible parts of a grain-producing plant.
An opening, usually covered by one or more panes of clear glass, to allow light and air from outside to enter a building or vehicle.
To furnish with windows.
A piece of clothing worn on the upper body outside a shirt or blouse, often waist length to thigh length.
To enclose or encase in a jacket or other covering.
To frighten, terrify, startle, especially in a minor way.
Feeling fear; afraid, frightened.
To stir the emotions of.
Having great enthusiasm.

To dress or adorn.

In need of some rest or sleep.

The basic taste sensation induced by sugar.

Used as a positive response to good news or information.
A series of sounds organized in time, employing melody, harmony, tempo etc. usually to convey a mood.
To seduce or entice with music.

To give something color.
Conveying color, as opposed to shades of gray.

An expression of mirth particular to the human species; the sound heard in laughing; laughter.

To show mirth, satisfaction, or derision, by peculiar movement of the muscles of the face, particularly of the mouth, causing a lighting up of the face and eyes, and usually accompanied by the emission of explosive or chuckling sounds from the chest and throat; to indulge in laughter.
A colorful, conspicuous structure associated with angiosperms, frequently scented and attracting various insects, and which may or may not be used for sexual reproduction.
To put forth blooms.
